Key Concepts :
1. Instance-Level Firewall
   Security Groups EC2 instance level par kaam karte hain
   Subnet level nahi, seedha instance par lagta hai
   Har instance mein ek ya multiple security groups ho sakte hain
   Ye decide karte hain ki kon sa traffic IN aayega aur kon sa traffic OUT jayega

2. Stateful Nature ⭐ (Exam ke liye MOST IMPORTANT!)
  Stateful ka matlab simple hai:
  Agar aapne inbound traffic allow kiya,to uska response automatically allow ho jayega!
Example:
  - User ne port 80 par request bheji (HTTP)
  - Aapne inbound mein port 80 allow kiya
  - Response automatically wapis jayegi
  - Aapko outbound rule banane ki zarurat NAHI hai!
    Kyunki Security Group "yaad rakhta hai" ki ye 
     connection already establish hua hai.


3. First Line of Defense
 EC2 instances ki sabse pehli security layer
 Network ACLs ke baad aati hai (jo subnet level par hoti hai)
 Ye soch lo jaise ghar ka main gate (NACLs) aur phir har kamre ka apna lock (Security Groups)

Important Features - Exam Ke Liye:
✅ Sirf ALLOW Rules
  Security Groups mein sirf ALLOW rules hote hain
  DENY rules NAHI bana sakte
  By default sab kuch DENY hai
  Jo explicitly allow karo, sirf wahi traffic aayegi

✅ Default Behavior
  Inbound Traffic: By default SAB DENY ❌
  Outbound Traffic: By default SAB ALLOW ✅
 Matlab instance bahar se kisi ko access nahi kar sakta initially, lekin instance khud bahar access kar sakta hai

✅ Multiple Security Groups
 Ek instance mein multiple SGs attach kar sakte ho
 Sabhi rules combine hokar kaam karte hain
 Agar ek SG mein SSH allow hai aur dusre mein HTTP, to dono allow honge

✅ Changes Immediately Apply
 Security Group mein changes turant apply hote hain
 Instance restart karne ki zarurat NAHI
 Real-time changes!

Security Groups vs Network ACLs (Exam Mein Zaroor Puchte Hain):
FeatureSecurity GroupsNetwork ACLsKaha lagta haiInstance levelSubnet levelStateful/StatelessStateful ✅Stateless ❌RulesSirf AllowAllow + Deny donoRule ProcessingSab rules check hoteNumber order meinReturn TrafficAuto allowExplicitly allow karna padtaDefaultAll DENY inboundCustom NACL = DENY all
Common Exam Scenarios:

Scenario 1: Web Server Setup
Inbound Rules:
- Port 80 (HTTP) - Allow from 0.0.0.0/0
- Port 443 (HTTPS) - Allow from 0.0.0.0/0
- Port 22 (SSH) - Allow from YOUR_IP only

Outbound:
- Default sab allow hai (stateful hai!)
Scenario 2: Database Server
Inbound Rules:
- Port 3306 (MySQL) - Allow from Web-Server-SG only
  (Security Group ID use karte hain source mein!)
  
Security ke liye:
- Direct internet access NAHI
- Sirf web server se connection

Scenario 3: Troubleshooting
Problem: Website access nahi ho raha
Check karo:
1. Security Group mein port 80/443 allow hai?
2. Inbound rules correct hain?
3. Source IP sahi hai? (0.0.0.0/0 ya specific IP)
4. NACL bhi check karo (stateless hai!)
Important Points - Exam Ke Liye Yaad Rakho:

Stateful = Return traffic automatically allow
Instance level protection
Allow rules only - deny nahi kar sakte
Changes immediate apply hote hain
Multiple SGs combine ho sakte hain
Source mein IP ya dusre SG ka reference de sakte ho
Default inbound DENY, outbound ALLOW

